<header class="article-header"><section class="title"><aside><ul class="tags"><li class=" first"><a class="accent-bg" href="nintendo-switch">Nintendo Switch</a></li><li><a class="accent-bg" href="tags/hori">Hori</a></li><li class=" last"><a class="accent-bg" href="tags/accessories">Accessories</a></li></ul>
</aside><h1 class="title"><a href="news/2020/08/hori_reveals_three_new_colours_for_its_split_pad_pro_switch_controller">Hori Reveals Three New Colours For Its Split Pad Pro Switch Controller</a></h1>
<p class="description">Pre-orders coming soon</p>
</section><section class="byline"><ul class="article-author"><li class=" first"><img class="avatar" src="https://images.nintendolife.com/users/79507/avatar.jpg" width="30" height="30" alt="Liam_Doolan" /></li><li class="authors last">by <a class="author-name" rel="nofollow" href="/users/Liam_Doolan">Liam Doolan</a> <span class="icon icon-time"></span> <time class="date age " datetime="2020-08-11T02:05:00+00:00"><span>Tue 11th Aug 2020</span></time></li></ul>
<ul class="share-this "><li class=" first">Share:</li><li class="value"><span class="accent-bg share-count">175</span><span class="icon icon-caret-right accent"></span></li><li><a class="ui-share-page whatsapp accent" title="Share this on WhatsApp" data-service="whatsapp" rel="nofollow" href="#"><span class="icon icon-whatsapp"></span></a></li><li><a class="ui-share-page facebook accent" title="Share this on Facebook" data-service="facebook" rel="nofollow" href="#"><span class="icon icon-facebook"></span></a></li><li><a class="ui-share-page twitter accent" title="Share this on Twitter" data-service="twitter" rel="nofollow" href="#"><span class="icon icon-twitter"></span></a></li><li><a class="ui-share-page messenger accent for-mobile" title="Share this on Facebook Messenger" data-service="fbmessenger" rel="nofollow" href="#"><span class="icon icon-messenger"></span></a></li><li class=" last"><a class="ui-share-page reddit accent for-desktop" title="Share this on Reddit" data-service="reddit" rel="nofollow" href="#"><span class="icon icon-reddit"></span></a></li></ul>
</section><div class="insert-label centered insert-mobile-sticky for-mobile"><div id="NL_MPU_MOB" data-ghost-zone="" data-dfp-id="NL_MPU_MOB" data-dfp-sizes="300x250,320x400" style="min-height:250px" data-dfp-targeting="experiment=nl-article-mobile-top"></div>
</div></header><div class="body body-text article-text"><section class="text">
<figure class="picture strip"><a title="Nintendo Switch" href="https://images.nintendolife.com/c5a1ef67dae1e/nintendo-switch.original.jpg"><img src="https://images.nintendolife.com/c5a1ef67dae1e/nintendo-switch.900x.jpg" width="900" height="506" alt="Nintendo Switch" /></a></figure><p>As fantastic as it is to play the Switch in handheld mode, the Joy-Con setup can become a little cramped from time to time. If you're seeking a more ergonomic gaming experience while you play Animal Crossing, Mario Kart or Zelda for hours on end, you can't go past the Split Pad Pro by peripheral maker Hori.</p>
<p>It was originally made available in one colour last October, <a href="https://www.nintendolife.com/news/2020/07/horis_pac-man_split_pad_pro_for_switch_is_so_gorgeous_we_want_to_gobble_it_up">got a special PAC-MAN design last month</a>, and on 7th September will receive three more colours: Transparent Black, Midnight Blue and Volcanic Red (priced at $49.99 USD each). Take a look:</p>
<aside class="object object-tweet"><blockquote class="twitter-tweet" align="center"><span lang="en" dir="ltr">Beef up your handheld experience with one of our NEW colors of the Split Pad Pro for Nintendo Switch. <br>ãƒ»Transparent Black<br>ãƒ»Midnight Blue<br>ãƒ»Volcanic Red<br>Pre-orders coming soon! <a href="https://twitter.com/hashtag/HORI?src=hash&amp;ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw">#HORI</a> <a href="https://twitter.com/hashtag/Switch?src=hash&amp;ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw">#Switch</a> <a href="https://twitter.com/hashtag/SplitPadPro?src=hash&amp;ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw">#SplitPadPro</a> <a href="https://t.co/M6KQQaIyRu">pic.twitter.com/M6KQQaIyRu</a></span>&mdash; HORI USA (@horiusainc) <a href="https://twitter.com/horiusainc/status/1292966753539174400?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw">August 10, 2020</a></blockquote>
<script async src="https://platform.twitter.com/widgets.js" charset="utf-8" type="27bd96246532d92b3a125a1b-text/javascript"></script>
</aside>
<p>As noted by Hori, preorders are coming soon - keep in mind this controller only works in handheld mode. Here's what else we had to say about the Split Pad Pro in <a href="https://www.nintendolife.com/news/2019/10/hardware_review_big_hands_meet_the_hori_split_pad_pro_for_switch">our hardware review</a> last year:</p>
<blockquote>
<p>Hori has come back with a new controller, catering once again to the Switchâ€™s Handheld player market: the Split Pad Pro. A larger, more ergonomic Joy-Con style controller that intends to give you the feeling of playing with a Pro Controller, but in <em>handheld</em> mode.</p></blockquote><div class="insert-label centered insert lazyload for-mobile lazyload"><div id="NL_MPU_X" data-ghost-zone="" data-dfp-id="NL_MPU_X" data-dfp-sizes="300x250,300x600" style="min-height:250px" class="lazyload" data-dfp-targeting="experiment=nl-article-mobile-1"></div>
</div><blockquote>
</blockquote>
