<section class="text">
<p>On paper I'd be all over these as I find the buttons on the joy-cons too small a lot of the time and I find my thumb often nudges the right analogue stick when I'm pushing the buttons.</p><p>But! The lack of gyro is a total interest killer for me, there's no way I'd want controllers without gyro, even if the larger sticks do allow for more accuracy. It's the macro speed of the analogue sticks combined with the micro accuracy of the gyro that makes them such a superb combination.</p></section>
