<article class="comment" id="comment5762125" data-author="users/150708" data-subject="comments/5762125" data-dislikes="0" data-id="5762125">
<p class="avatar"><a rel="nofollow" title="rjc-32" href="/users/rjc-32"><img class="framed lazy" src="data:image/svg+xml;base64,PHN2ZyB4bWxucz0iaHR0cDovL3d3dy53My5vcmcvMjAwMC9zdmciIHZpZXdCb3g9IjAgMCA4MCA4MCI+PC9zdmc+" width="80" height="80" data-original="https://static.nintendolife.com/themes/nl.v10/images/avatar.jpg" alt="rjc-32" /></a></p>
<div class="detail"><ul class="info"><li class=" first"><a class="num" rel="nofollow" href="news/2020/08/hori_reveals_three_new_colours_for_its_split_pad_pro_switch_controller#comment5762125">63</a></li><li><a rel="nofollow" class="username accent" title="rjc-32" href="/users/rjc-32">rjc-32</a></li><li class=" last"><time class="date age " datetime="2020-08-11T16:08:13+00:00"><span>Tue 11th Aug 2020</span></time></li></ul>
<section class="text">
<p>Hori make great grips and alternative controllers. I am very happy to own the Monster Hunter XX grip for 3DS, along with the Remote Play Assist for Vita. Both of these have gotten ridiculously expensive in the past year, over 150 for each, crazy. They are excellent products though, they transform the handhelds from uncomfortable, cramp inducing wrecks to ergonomic delights! I love the Split Pad Pro, my only wish is that the DPad was a little further to the left.</p>
</section>
